front_matter:
  id: pm-30lh
  title: "M5 follow-up: validate extension hook registration handlers"
  description: Harden extension API hook registration so non-function handlers fail activation deterministically.
  type: Task
  status: closed
  priority: 1
  tags[6]: "area:extensions",code,"milestone:5",pm-cli,"priority:1",tests
  created_at: "2026-03-04T19:12:46.724Z"
  updated_at: "2026-03-04T19:31:06.396Z"
  deadline: "2026-03-06T23:59:00.000Z"
  author: cursor-maintainer
  estimated_minutes: 75
  acceptance_criteria: "Non-function hook registrations fail extension activation deterministically, docs are aligned, and regression tests plus pm test/pm test-all sweeps pass with 100% coverage."
  dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
    pm-b1w,parent,"2026-03-04T19:12:46.724Z",cursor-maintainer,null
  comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
    "2026-03-04T19:12:46.724Z",cursor-maintainer,This task closes runtime hardening gaps for malformed hook registration payloads in JS extensions.
    "2026-03-04T19:12:56.109Z",cursor-maintainer,"Planned changeset: docs-first update PRD and README to require hook registration handler validation, then enforce runtime function checks for api.hooks registrations in extension loader and add extension-loader regression tests."
    "2026-03-04T19:14:01.682Z",cursor-maintainer,"Docs-first update complete: PRD and README now require registration-time validation for hook handlers with deterministic activation failure semantics."
    "2026-03-04T19:30:57.032Z",cursor-maintainer,"Implemented docs-first + code changeset: updated PRD.md and README.md to define registration-time hook handler validation, added runtime function checks for api.hooks.beforeCommand/afterCommand/onWrite/onRead/onIndex in src/core/extensions/loader.ts, and extended tests/unit/extension-loader.spec.ts with invalid-hook activation regressions for all hook registration APIs."
    "2026-03-04T19:30:57.210Z",cursor-maintainer,"Evidence: pm test pm-30lh --run --timeout 7200 --json passed 2/2 linked tests (coverage + targeted extension-loader suite). pm test-all --status in_progress --timeout 7200 --json passed totals items=1 linked_tests=2 passed=2 failed=0 skipped=0. pm test-all --status closed --timeout 7200 --json passed totals items=54 linked_tests=179 passed=56 failed=0 skipped=123. Coverage statement: node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage reports 100% statements/branches/functions/lines. Follow-up items created: none."
  notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
    "2026-03-04T19:12:46.724Z",cursor-maintainer,Update docs first then enforce hook registration function checks and extend extension-loader tests.
  learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
    "2026-03-04T19:12:46.724Z",cursor-maintainer,Runtime guardrails are required even when TypeScript signatures exist because extensions execute as JavaScript.
  files[4]{path,scope,note}:
    PRD.md,project,docs-first hook validation contract
    README.md,project,docs-first public behavior update
    src/core/extensions/loader.ts,project,hook registration runtime validation
    tests/unit/extension-loader.spec.ts,project,regression coverage for invalid hook registration
  tests[2]{command,path,scope,timeout_seconds,note}:
    node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage,null,project,7200,coverage gate
    node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extension-loader.spec.ts,null,project,1800,targeted extension loader regression
  docs[3]{path,scope,note}:
    AGENTS.md,project,dogfood workflow requirements
    PRD.md,project,extension registration contract
    README.md,project,public extension behavior contract
body: Add runtime validation for api.hooks.beforeCommand/afterCommand/onWrite/onRead/onIndex registration inputs so malformed JS extensions fail during activation with deterministic warnings.
